    <h1>Customer Journey Mapping for a Commercial Insurance Application Process</h1>
        <p>Team: Philippe Meister</p>
        <p>This page summarizes the work. The work can be presented in more detail upon request.</p>
    <h3>Summary</h3>
      <p>The UX and commercial lines teams conducted customer journey mapping of participants experiences form the time they sent PDF applicaitons for new business to the time the business was issued. Customer journey mapping is a technique that allows us to devleop knoweldge about customers' expereriences as they move through a process.</p>
      <p>The methods used to achive the outcome were internal and external interviews. First, we interviewed four comemrcial lines underwriters and developed an internal assumption customer journey map. The internal assumption map represented our internal understaing of hte process. Second, we interviewer 12 external particiapnts to develop a reserach=based customer jorurney map. The resrach-based map verified some internal knoweldge and helped us develop new knoweldge of our customers' experiences with the applicaiton process. The reserach-based map described the steps in the process, needs, positive aspects, and opportuniites for improvement. The potential improvements were listed and provided to the commercial lines leadership to inform their decision making. </p> 
